<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 17 mm, female 17-19 mm. The triangle of golden pile on the mesoscutum place this species in a group with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aureoscutus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aureoscutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. aureoscutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aureus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aureus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. aureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. trilinea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="trilinea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. trilinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. trivittatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="trivittatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. trivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Peradon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peradon fenestratus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fenestratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peradon fenestratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all four of those by the erect (instead of appressed) pile on the scutellum (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 13–18" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 13 - 18. 13 - 15 Mesoscutum: 13 Peradon aureoscutus male holotype 14 P. aureus male Ecuador CNC 15 P. trivittatus male French Guiana RMNH 16 Peradon fenestratus, scutellum lateral 17, 18 Tergites 2 and 3: 17 Peradon trilinea male holotype 18 P. aureus male holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures13-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362275" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures13-18">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
